subSubSection.paragraph:
Though a pair of salivary glands indeed inserts into the pharynx on the sides of the oesophagus, the knowledge of these is limited only to a few species (e.g., 
MacFarland, 1966
; 
Valdes & Bouchet, 1998
; 
Pola & Stout, 2008
). The salivary glands are usually not figured in the original descriptions (an exception: 
Valdes and Bouchet, 1998
) and were never consistently used for taxonomic diagnostics. We therefore do not include salivary glands in the diagnoses of the species of the genus 

Dendronotus

.
